column4: I have an USB external SATA drive dock. I hooked it up and the disk has been spinning several minutes, but I have no indication the drive has actually been mounted. How should I proceed?
sudo fdisk -l , is it found ?
It doesn't look like it.
also not under places > removable ...
No.
re-plug it, pastebin the output of dmesg | tail
http://paste.ubuntu.com/607254/
sudo fdisk -l , devicename ?
http://paste.ubuntu.com/607256/
is 8 G size of the usb ?
maybe an old raid ? sudo gparted, or is there data expected on the external drive ?
It wasn't in a RAID array.
There is data expected.
I had it hooked up internally fine.
sata.. hmm, jumpers on it ?
Works when hooked up to my laptop, so I doubt that's it. I hesitate to pull it while it's ostensibly spinning.
Ope, think I found something that suffices.
I had tried two USB ports, both that bounced off the internal hub.
Plugging in to the back of the box seems to work.
just to be sure, usb-utils installed ? ah, ic
look up your bios, if legacy support is on and all hubs are activated, though dmesg found it
Thanks.
welcome
